The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 One of the most towering personalities of Indian classical music of our times, Pandit Vijay Kichlu has revived the age-old guru-shishya parampara as the founder-director of ITC Sangeet Research Academy. Dedicating himself towards preserving the rich traditions of Indian classical music, he introduced the concept of recorded music lessons, which greatly benefited students, professionals and teachers alike. In celebration of his 75th birth anniversary, Devgandharva hosts a classical music concert, featuring recitals by celebrated artistes. Shivkumar Sharma will present a santoor recital, accompanied by Anindo Chatterjee (tabla). This will be followed by a duet thumri recital by Birju Maharaj and Girija Devi, with Kishan Maharaj (tabla). The evening will also be witness to the launch of the first two albums of the complete educational series on Indian classical music prepared by Pandit Vijay Kichlu.

